        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "h2"
    },
    {
      "_key": "62880f621e55",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "517ad88d0c850",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Set the initial "
        },
        {
          "_key": "d237185952cb",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "strong"
          ],
          "text": "Value"
        },
        {
          "_key": "22d7bf5dfad6",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": " as a valid hexadecimal colour. By default this is stop 500, but it can be changed to any stop from 50-950."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "b001ae72dbfe",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "b338a27492600",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "For colours that have 100% "
        },
        {
          "_key": "b338a27492601",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "strong"
          ],
          "text": "Saturation"
        },
        {
          "_key": "b338a27492602",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": ", make the Palette more interesting by shifting the "
        },
        {
          "_key": "b338a27492603",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "strong"
          ],
          "text": "Hue"
        },
        {
          "_key": "b338a27492604",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": " up or down."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "abfb4ed455b1",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "5f80a82aecd80",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Palettes starting from a Base colour with little "
        },
        {
          "_key": "5f80a82aecd81",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "strong"
          ],
          "text": "Saturation"
        },
        {
          "_key": "5f80a82aecd82",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": " get more interesting by increasing "
        },
        {
          "_key": "5f80a82aecd83",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "strong"
          ],
          "text": "Saturation"
        },
        {
          "_key": "5f80a82aecd84",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": " at the extremes."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "1b0eab32d2a7",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "9afa7bb559a40",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Shift the "
        },
        {
          "_key": "9afa7bb559a41",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "strong"
          ],
          "text": "Minimum/Maximum"
        },
        {
          "_key": "9afa7bb559a42",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Â "
        },
        {
          "_key": "9afa7bb559a43",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "strong"
          ],
          "text": "Lightness/Luminance"
        },
        {
          "_key": "9afa7bb559a44",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": " to spread out the rest of the colours to the extremes of white and black. Switch between Lightness and Luminance to produce a different spread of colours at the extremes."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "15179d4ddf89",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "fb06f34e0b5f0",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "These principles are inspired by the excellent "
        },
        {
          "_key": "fb06f34e0b5f1",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [
            "406cb32abaaa"
          ],
          "text": "Refactoring UI"
        },
        {
          "_key": "fb06f34e0b5f2",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": " book by Adam Wathan & Steve Schoger. The same book recommends against automated tools, just like this one!"
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
        {
          "_key": "406cb32abaaa",
          "_type": "link",
          "href": "https://refactoringui.com/book/"
        }
      ],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "d25d56cd2819",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "60a917f8ee250",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "This tool exists to fast-track the creation of new palettes."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "d549e0455120",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "25647bae0b590",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Palette API"
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "h2"
    },
    {
      "_key": "863c1d603ba2",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "fccfa03b840f0",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Any set of Palettes can be fetched via an API. You may find this useful for design tools that need to generate a 50-950 Palette from just a single Hex value."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "aa907009568f",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "b66cb0331a4a",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Currently, the API will only return a Palette using the base hex value, with no options to have HSL tweaks."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
